I like Klopp in general but the guy exaggerates anything and everything. Don't even know whether he's being sincere or patronizing, it's bad either way. Solskjaer is similar tho he comes across as deluded more often than not.

Lampard has the best tact amongst all of them and he balances candour, brevity and delicacy very well. Surprising since he's only been managing for less than 2 years, so that makes it even more impressive.
